There is a law which guarantees
The breaking of the dawn;
No matter how the night may press,
The light will carry on.

For every shadow, there’s a flame;
For every tear, a smile;
Though weary bones forget your name,
You’re held a little while.

So walk the path with steady trust,
And let your worries ease;
The world is fair, and kind, and just—
There is a law which guarantees.

The river led me to you though the way was hard and long,
With every mile I questioned if the journey would go wrong.
But water knows the secret paths, and listens to the heart;
It carried me with gentle force, it knew right from the start.
Now here I am, beside you, my wandering at an end;
The river’s path was difficult, but led me to my friend.
